  "prompt": "Which is the best DSLR under 2500?",
  "response": "As of my last update, there are several good DSLR cameras available for under $2500. The choice depends on your specific needs and preferences, such as image quality, ease of use, and the type of photography you plan to do. Here are a few options that are often recommended in this price range:\n\n1. **Canon EOS 6D Mark II**:\n   - Full-frame sensor\n   - 26.2 MP image quality\n   - Dual Pixel CMOS AF\n   - Vari-angle touchscreen\n   - Good low-light performance\n\n2. **Nikon D780**:\n   - Full-frame sensor\n   - 24.5 MP image quality\n   - Excellent autofocus system\n   - 4K video recording capabilities\n\n3. **Pentax K-1 Mark II**:\n   - Full-frame sensor\n   - 36.4 MP image quality\n   - Stellar build quality with weather-sealing\n   - Pixel Shift Resolution feature for higher detail\n\n4. **Canon EOS 90D**:\n   - APS-C sensor\n   - 32.5 MP image quality\n   - Fast autofocus with Dual Pixel CMOS AF\n   - 10 fps continuous shooting\n   - 4K video\n\n5. **Nikon D500**:\n   - APS-C sensor\n   - 20.9 MP image quality\n   - Extremely fast 10 fps continuous shooting\n   - Rugged, weather-sealed body\n\nThese cameras are well-suited for a range of photography styles, from portrait to sports to landscape. When deciding, consider factors like sensor size (APS-C vs. full-frame), resolution, video capabilities, and brand ecosystem, including lens options and other accessories you might need. Always check the latest reviews and prices, as they can fluctuate over time.",
